Effective Date: February 28, 2025
Privacy and security are very important to us at Plaid. This End User Privacy Policy (‚ÄúPolicy‚Äù) is meant to help you (the ‚Äúend user‚Äù) understand how we at Plaid collect, use, and share your data when you use Plaid products or services - for example, when you use Plaid Portal, or when you use Plaid to connect and share your data to power the applications (‚Äúapps‚Äù) you use. These apps, which offer many consumer services and products such as helping you save for retirement, manage your spending, streamline credit applications, or transfer money, are built and provided by our business customers (we‚Äôll call them ‚Äúdevelopers‚Äù here), and powered by Plaid.
This Policy applies to Plaid Inc., Plaid Financial Ltd., and Plaid, B.V. (collectively, ‚ÄúPlaid,‚Äù ‚Äúwe,‚Äù ‚Äúour,‚Äù and ‚Äúus‚Äù). Please see the
‚ÄúContacting Plaid‚Äù
section below for which of these entities is responsible for processing your data. This Policy does not cover services offered by Plaid Consumer Reporting Agency, Inc. (‚ÄúPlaid CRA‚Äù); for more information on that policy please see the
CRA Privacy Policy
.
You should read this Policy carefully, it contains important information about your privacy rights and choices.
